  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Felony charges\n- Significant prison time (typically 5-20 years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset seizure\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Additional consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nThe specific punishment depends on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Jurisdiction\n- Prior criminal history\n- Specific circumstances of the crime\n\nProsecution typically involves law enforcement agencies like the FBI, IRS, and federal prosecutors.",
